Genotype concordance ci was defined as: 1 if both genotypes match (xi1 = yi1and xi2 = yi2 or xi2 = yi1and xi1 = yi2); 0 if neither imputed allele matched a true allele; else 0.5 if one but not both imputed alleles matched the true alleles. Genotype concordance for an STR is the average over all the samples \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
